body:
5.040 errors out with `%Error: Internal Error: dfg_internal_error_multiple_uses.sv:5:18: ../V3DfgDfgToAst.cpp:151: Intermediate DFG value with multiple uses` on RTL that was accepted (though with an UNOPTFLAT warning) on 5.038.

The below minimized example fails on 5.040 with the internal error noted above.
It passes on 5.038, but has an UNOPTFLAT warning: `%Warning-UNOPTFLAT: dfg_internal_error_multiple_uses.sv:5:18: Signal unoptimizable: Circular combinational logic: 'dfg_internal_error_multiple_uses.x'
    5 |     logic [31:0] x[ARRAY_SIZE];`

```verilog
module dfg_internal_error_multiple_uses (
    output logic out
);
    localparam int ARRAY_SIZE = 3;
    logic [31:0] x[ARRAY_SIZE];

    assign x[0] = '1;

    genvar i,j;
    for (j = 1; j < ARRAY_SIZE; j = j + 1) begin
        localparam int IN_WIDTH = j + 1;
        localparam int OUT_WIDTH = j + 2;
        localparam int ADDERS = 32/(2**(j+1));
        for (i = 0; i < ADDERS; i = i + 1) begin
            assign x[j][OUT_WIDTH*i +: OUT_WIDTH] =
                x[j-1][2*IN_WIDTH*i          +: IN_WIDTH] +
                x[j-1][2*IN_WIDTH*i+IN_WIDTH +: IN_WIDTH];
        end
    end

    assign out = ^x[ARRAY_SIZE-1];

endmodule
```

The below two examples pass on 5.040 with no warnings or errors. Note that one of these changes `x` to a packed array and the other keeps `x` unpacked but only has an unpacked dimension of 2. Seemingly all unpacked ARRAY_SIZE >= 3 fail with the internal error.
These two examples both have an UNOPTFLAT warning on 5.038.

```verilog
module no_error_packed_array (
    output logic out
);
    localparam int ARRAY_SIZE = 3;
    logic [ARRAY_SIZE-1:0][31:0] x;

    assign x[0] = '1;

    genvar i,j;
    for (j = 1; j < ARRAY_SIZE; j = j + 1) begin
        localparam int IN_WIDTH = j + 1;
        localparam int OUT_WIDTH = j + 2;
        localparam int ADDERS = 32/(2**(j+1));
        for (i = 0; i < ADDERS; i = i + 1) begin
            assign x[j][OUT_WIDTH*i +: OUT_WIDTH] =
                x[j-1][2*IN_WIDTH*i          +: IN_WIDTH] +
                x[j-1][2*IN_WIDTH*i+IN_WIDTH +: IN_WIDTH];
        end
    end

    assign out = ^x[ARRAY_SIZE-1];

endmodule
```

```verilog
module no_error_array_size_2 (
    output logic out
);
    localparam int ARRAY_SIZE = 2;
    logic [31:0] x[ARRAY_SIZE];

    assign x[0] = '1;

    genvar i,j;
    for (j = 1; j < ARRAY_SIZE; j = j + 1) begin
        localparam int IN_WIDTH = j + 1;
        localparam int OUT_WIDTH = j + 2;
        localparam int ADDERS = 32/(2**(j+1));
        for (i = 0; i < ADDERS; i = i + 1) begin
            assign x[j][OUT_WIDTH*i +: OUT_WIDTH] =
                x[j-1][2*IN_WIDTH*i          +: IN_WIDTH] +
                x[j-1][2*IN_WIDTH*i+IN_WIDTH +: IN_WIDTH];
        end
    end

    assign out = ^x[ARRAY_SIZE-1];

endmodule
```

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?
verilator --lint-only file.sv

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
5.040 and 5.038. Have not tried with master but can if needed.

What OS and distribution are you using?
RHEL9

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?
No, sorry.

